#
#  onlyargs distinctive features:
#    - SPLIT-CRATE design — `onlyargs` core crate provides the
#      trait + macros (zero proc-macros, only stdlib `parse_macro_
#      input!`-style declarative); separate `onlyargs_derive`
#      provides the `#[derive(OnlyArgs)]` proc-macro for
#      convenience.  Users can pick which.
#    - `impl_help!()` and `impl_version!()` declarative macros —
#      generate the HELP and VERSION constants from doc-comments
#      and Cargo.toml metadata at COMPILE TIME (read via
#      `env!("CARGO_PKG_VERSION")` etc.)
#    - DOC-COMMENT-AS-HELP — `/// description` doc-comments above
#      struct fields become per-flag --help text; description of
#      the struct itself becomes the program description; footer
#      lines via `#[footer = "..."]` attributes
#    - FIELD ATTRIBUTES (derive only):
#      * `#[short]` — register a single-char short flag (auto-
#        derived from first letter, or explicit via
#        `#[short('X')]`)
#      * `#[long]` — register the long flag (default behavior;
#        explicit when overriding the snake_case-to-kebab-case
#        conversion)
#      * `#[positional]` — positional argument instead of flag
#      * `#[default(...)]` — default value when flag absent
#    - TYPE INFERENCE from struct field types:
#      * `bool` → boolean flag (presence = true; no value)
#      * `Option<T>` → optional flag
#      * `Vec<T>` → REPEATABLE flag (each occurrence appends)
#      * `PathBuf` / `OsString` → path/OsString-typed value
#      * Numeric primitives (`u32`/`i64`/`f64`) → parsed from
#        string via FromStr
#      * Custom types implementing `FromStr` → custom-parsed
#    - `CliError` enum — `Unknown(OsString)` / `Missing(name)` /
#      `Invalid(name, value)` / `ParseError(err)` variants for
#      parse failures
#    - `Self::help()` / `Self::version()` convenience methods on
#      the trait — print HELP/VERSION constants and `process::
#      exit(0)`
#    - INSPIRED BY clap_derive (struct-based schema) but WAY
#      smaller; explicitly designed for users who want
#      "structopt without the dependencies"
#    - NO SUBCOMMAND SUPPORT — onlyargs is FLAT-SCHEMA only; for
#      hierarchical subcommands, caller dispatches manually based
#      on first positional + re-parses with a different Args
#      struct
#    - NO ANSI COLORS in help output — minimalism extends to
#      output rendering
#    - NO suggest-similar-flag ("Did you mean: --foo?") — just
#      hard error on unknown flag
#    - NO auto-help-on-error formatting — caller prints HELP
#      constant on Err in main()
